---
import AboutHeroImage from "../assets/dw_dogs.jpg";
import ResumePDF from "../assets/DanielWestfall_Resume.pdf";
import Layout from "../layouts/BlogPost.astro";
---
  <div class="about-content">
    <div class="resume-actions" style="display:flex;gap:1rem;justify-content:center;margin:1rem 0;">
      <a class="download-resume" href={ResumePDF} download="DanielWestfall_Resume.pdf" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Download Daniel Westfall resume as PDF">
        <md-filled-tonal-button>Download Resume (PDF)</md-filled-tonal-button>
      </a>
      <a class="view-resume" href={ResumePDF} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="Open Daniel Westfall resume in new tab">
        <md-text-button>Open Resume</md-text-button>
      </a>
    </div>

    <md-elevated-card class="about-section">
      <div class="card-content">
        <section aria-labelledby="summary-heading">
          <h2 id="summary-heading">Professional Summary</h2>
          <p><strong>Certified Digital Accessibility Leader</strong> (CPWA, Trusted Tester) with 4+ years of progressive experience specializing in <strong>accessibility governance</strong>, <strong>inclusive product strategy</strong>, and technical execution. Expert in implementing and enforcing compliance with <strong>WCAG 2.2 AA standards</strong> across large-scale digital platforms. Proven ability to lead cross-functional teams by providing expert technical guidance (WAI-ARIA, HTML, CSS, JavaScript) and conducting rigorous manual accessibility testing (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver) throughout the entire product development lifecycle.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </md-elevated-card>

    <md-elevated-card class="about-section">
      <div class="card-content">
        <section aria-labelledby="expertise-heading">
          <h2 id="expertise-heading">Technical Expertise</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Design Systems:</strong> Accessible UI Components, design documentation, technical specifications, cross-functional design/eng partnership.</li>
            <li><strong>Testing & Auditing:</strong> Manual accessibility testing (Trusted Tester methodology), automated scanning (WAVE, axe Dev Tools), compliance audits, usability testing with AT users.</li>
            <li><strong>Assistive Technology:</strong> JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver (iOS/macOS), TalkBack, ChromeVox, keyboard-only navigation.</li>
            <li><strong>Standards & Governance:</strong> WCAG 2.2 (A/AA/AAA), Section 508, ARIA, VPAT/ACR creation, PDF remediation.</li>
            <li><strong>Development & Tools:</strong> HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript, WAI-ARIA, VS Code, GitHub, Asana.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </md-elevated-card>

    <md-elevated-card class="about-section">
      <div class="card-content">
        <section aria-labelledby="experience-heading">
          <h2 id="experience-heading">Professional Experience</h2>

          <article class="job-entry">
            <header>
              <h3>Digital Accessibility Manager</h3>
              <p><strong>QuaverEd</strong> | Nashville, TN</p>
              <p><time datetime="2024-10">October 2024</time> – <time>Present</time></p>
            </header>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Led accessibility strategy and governance</strong>, implementing policies that drove the adoption of inclusive design and development practices across product and engineering teams.</li>
              <li>Provided expert technical leadership and consulting by delivering validated HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and WAI-ARIA code samples and detailed technical specifications for compliant front-end implementation.</li>
              <li>Managed the quality assurance of design system components through continuous audit and refinement, ensuring high standards for all new UI components.</li>
              <li>Conducted extensive manual accessibility testing with multiple ATs (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver) to ensure the quality and usability of new features and component updates.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="job-entry">
            <header>
              <h3>Accessibility Audit Team Lead</h3>
              <p><strong>QuaverEd</strong> | Nashville, TN</p>
              <p><time datetime="2023-04">April 2023</time> – <time datetime="2024-10">October 2024</time></p>
            </header>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Directed and executed comprehensive accessibility audits</strong> for large digital resources (web apps, multimedia), ensuring strict adherence to WCAG 2.2 AA and Section 508.</li>
              <li>Developed and led internal workshops and training programs on WCAG and best practices, significantly building organizational capacity and expertise.</li>
              <li>Authored and maintained detailed Accessibility Conformance Reports (ACRs) and VPATs, providing essential compliance documentation for large institutional stakeholders.</li>
              <li>Translated complex compliance requirements into clear, actionable feedback and development priorities for engineering and creative teams.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="job-entry">
            <header>
              <h3>Accessibility Auditor</h3>
              <p><strong>QuaverEd</strong> | Nashville, TN</p>
              <p><time datetime="2022-08">August 2022</time> – <time datetime="2023-04">April 2023</time></p>
            </header>
            <ul>
              <li>Performed hands-on manual testing of web applications using multiple assistive technologies (JAWS, NVDA, VoiceOver) across Windows, macOS, and ChromeOS, validating screen reader compatibility.</li>
              <li>Collaborated directly with customers and external contractors with disabilities to validate component usability and improve user experience.</li>
              <li>Created precise, prioritized remediation tickets for development teams, significantly bridging the technical knowledge gap between design and implementation.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="job-entry">
            <header>
              <h3>Calibration Technician</h3>
              <p><strong>K&amp;S Associates</strong> | Nashville, TN</p>
              <p><time datetime="2022-04">April 2022</time> – <time datetime="2022-08">August 2022</time></p>
            </header>
            <ul>
              <li>Conducted a variety of radiation therapy calibrations with a focus on accuracy and precision.</li>
              <li>Developed comprehensive reports about completed calibrations, ensuring all relevant stakeholders had access to necessary information.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>

          <article class="job-entry">
            <header>
              <h3>Manager and Founder</h3>
              <p><strong>Coffee Talk</strong> | Olathe, KS</p>
              <p><time datetime="2018-03">March 2018</time> – <time datetime="2021-07">July 2021</time></p>
            </header>
            <ul>
              <li>Optimized coffee shop layout for better customer flow, seating capacity, and a welcoming vibe.</li>
              <li>Built a user-friendly website and managed social media, boosting online engagement and inquiries.</li>
              <li>Championed accessibility in both physical and digital spaces, ensuring ADA compliance and inclusivity.</li>
            </ul>
          </article>
        </section>
      </div>
    </md-elevated-card>

    <md-elevated-card class="about-section">
      <div class="card-content">
        <section aria-labelledby="certs-heading">
          <h2 id="certs-heading">Certifications & Education</h2>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>CPWA</strong> (IAAP) — combined credential demonstrating CPACC + WAS</li>
            <li><strong>Web Accessibility Specialist (WAS)</strong> — IAAP</li>
            <li><strong>CPACC</strong> — IAAP</li>
            <li><strong>Trusted Tester Certification</strong> — U.S. Department of Homeland Security (TT-2204-02664)</li>
            <li><strong>Assistive Technology Certifications</strong> — Freedom Scientific / NV Access (JAWS, NVDA)</li>
            <li><strong>Google UX Design Certificate</strong> — Coursera/Google</li>
            <li><strong>MERN Full Stack Web Development</strong> — MIT xPro</li>
            <li><strong>Associate of Arts in Multimedia and Web Design</strong> — Art Institute of Atlanta</li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </div>
    </md-elevated-card>
